	<h1> There are three ways to add css to HTML</h1>
	<div>
		The first wat is to use style as an element inside a tag<br />
		For example:
	<p style="background-color:green;">background color of this text is green</p>
	<p style="background-color:red;">but this one is red</p>
	<p style="background-color:yellow">and this one is yellow</p>
	<p style="background-color:orange; font-size:20px;">
		you can also change the font size
	</p>
	<p style="font-family:arial; font-size:30px;">
		it is possible to change the font family too
	</p>
	<p style="font-size:30px; text-align:right; background-color:green; color:red ">
		And also you can change the text alignment
	</p>
	<p style="font-size:34px; color:orange; background-color:purple; text-align:center;   ">
		It is very nice to change the color of the font too

	</p>


</div>









